{
  "stem": "13219.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This is during the war, yes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is 1940-- beginning of 1945.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember going to Italy-- taking a train to Villach.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And from Villach you walked.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We used to exchange money and bring it back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this is how I made a living.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I'll go to Budapest and come back to Austria.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You didn't have papers at that time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The only thing I had is that I live in-- that my name is Gershkowitz, and I live in the DP camp in Bindermichl.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's all.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the thing was staatenlos.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That means I have-- didn't have no state.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we had a good time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- what can you do?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's been a long time, and you know, you got to live.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Have you-- while you were in Bindermichl, did you learn anything about what was going on in Poland with the Jewish people?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We did.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And matter of fact, the first thing we, we had to do is find out if they know about me in America because I have an aunt with a family and an uncle with a family.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And finally, they find out that we're there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they send us papers to come to America.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was in 1945.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- because the UNRRA used to send lists of names to America from the survivors.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's how my family here find out that we were alive.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then they started to work with the consulate here to see if they can take us out because we were ready to go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was-- to Palestine, at that time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were on the list to go to Palestine till we got papers that we could go to America.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sure because we had already people with the numbers in our camps.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
